      "id": "M1",
      "title": "Introduction to Cloud Computing and AWS",
      "description": "This module provides a foundational understanding of cloud computing concepts, benefits, and deployment models. It introduces the AWS platform, its global infrastructure, and key services. Topics include: What is Cloud Computing?, AWS Core Services Overview, AWS Global Infrastructure, AWS Management Console and CLI, and Setting up an AWS Account."
    },
    {
      "id": "M2",
      "title": "AWS S3 Deep Dive: Storage Fundamentals",
      "description": "This module focuses on AWS Simple Storage Service (S3). Learners will gain practical experience in creating, configuring, and managing S3 buckets. Topics include: S3 Bucket Creation and Configuration, Object Storage and Management, S3 Security and Access Control, S3 Versioning and Lifecycle Policies, and S3 Use Cases and Best Practices."
    },
    {
      "id": "M3",
      "title": "Compute and Networking Essentials",
      "description": "This module introduces fundamental compute and networking services in AWS. Learners will explore EC2 for virtual machines and VPC for network configuration. Topics include: Introduction to Amazon EC2, Launching and Managing EC2 Instances, Introduction to Amazon VPC, VPC Networking Components (Subnets, Route Tables, Gateways), and Security Groups and Network ACLs."
    },
    {
      "id": "M4",
      "title": "AWS Identity, Security, and Next Steps",
      "description": "This module covers AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) for secure access control and provides guidance on next steps for continued learning and career development. Topics include: AWS IAM Users, Groups, and Roles, IAM Policies and Best Practices, AWS Security Best Practices, Monitoring and Logging (CloudWatch), and Resources for Continued Learning and Career Advancement."
